{"title":"Chiru Bikes Nanulak Long Tail Ti Fat Bike","link":"https://theradavist.com/chiru-bikes-nanulak-long-tail-ti-fat-bike/","date":1740670350000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-02.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-02.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-02.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-02.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em><a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/chiru-bikes/\" target=\"_blank\">Chiru Bikes</a>, the French brand specializing in titanium solutions, has launched its Nanulak long-tail titanium <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/our-favorite-fat-bike-reviews-2024/\" target=\"_blank\">fat bike model</a> ahead of the Iditarod Trail Invitational in Alaska. This release has framebuilders rejoicing. Let’s see why below…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-01.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-01.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-01.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-01.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-03.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-03.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-03.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-03.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>From Custom Only to Production</h3>\n<p>Prior to the Nanulak, there wasn’t a production offering for long-tail titanium fat bikes. <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/meriwether-cycles-shop-visit/\" target=\"_blank\">Only available through custom framebuilders before this</a>, which would cost multitudes of $5,000-8,000 and up for a frame, the Nanulak brings the long-tail chassis model to the masses with a 2890 € price tag.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-05.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-05.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-05.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-05.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Chiru Nanulak Geometry</h3>\n<p>Available in three sizes, all with similar seat, head angles, and bottom bracket drops, the Chiru Nanulak is tuned for comfort during long expedition riding and racing.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-04.jpeg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-04.jpeg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-04.jpeg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Chiru-Bikes-Nanulak-Long-Tail-Fat-Bike-04.jpeg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Q Factor and Wheel Adaptability</h3>\n<p>The most distinctive feature of the Chiru Nanulak is the crank and bottom bracket interface that enables seamless switching between a fat bike Q factor crank suitable for 26×5.0″ tires and a narrower Q Factor crank compatible with 29×3.0 tires, giving the Nanulak exceptional versatility.</p>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://www.chirubikes.com/en/kit-cadre/nanulak/\" target=\"_blank\">Chiru Bikes</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/chiru-bikes-nanulak-long-tail-ti-fat-bike/\">Chiru Bikes Nanulak Long Tail Ti Fat Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"f46a4b9a0fe7736d26837cff40880075f00fab6e2845309088d9f744b9b197af","category":"Cycling"}